<h1>Introduction</h1>
<p>Our NGO was created with a vision of complex community care for people with mental illness. Our objective is a system of community mental care, which would enable the integration of people suffering from mental illness into their community.</p>
<p>Our activities are also directed at preventing stigmatization of people with mental illness and promotion of community care as an important part of mental health care.</p>
<h2>Our beginnings</h2>
<p>The NGO „KOMPAS – Komunitna pomoc a starostlivost“ (Community care and assistance) was registered at the district office in Trnava on <span style="font-weight: bold">September 19, 2008</span>.</p>
<h2>Who we are</h2>
<p>Founding members of our NGO are mental health professionals – two psychiatrists and a psychologist with experience in the field of mental health care, both with people suffering from mental illness and their relatives.</p>
<h2>Our goals</h2>
<p>To better address the issues of mental health care within the context of the mental health care reform in the Slovak republic.</p>